                <h1>Narcotics Anonymous: A Path to Recovery</h1>
                <p>Narcotics Anonymous (NA) was founded in 1953 as a fellowship of individuals seeking recovery from addiction to narcotics. Emphasizing anonymity and mutual support, NA operates under a 12-step program similar to Alcoholics Anonymous. It provides a safe space for sharing experiences and fostering healing through community connections.</p>
